description: Killing snakes due to fear of snake bites, Skin of pythons, cobra uses as lucrative commercial products, religious misconceptions are the noticeable reason of population declining. Lacking proper knowledge about them we can't recognize which are venomous and not. Some people in our community believed that all snakes are venomous and harmful to us. It was the horrible death of a cobra. This world wide least concern species named monocled cobra died by terrible hit of a bamboo stick in my area. But decreasing snakes is not good for our ecosystem. We have to change our misconceptions   by concerning their ecological value.
